    "tags": ["Iran Hormuz shoot-to-kill", "Spain NATO suspension", "EU Russia 20th sanctions", "EU Ukraine 90 billion"],
    "fresh": true,
    "content": "**Geopolitiks Snacks** — April 24, 2026\n\n---\n\n## 🎯 Trump Ordered the Military to Shoot Iranian Boats Laying Mines\n\nWhile extending the Israel-Lebanon ceasefire by three weeks, Trump also ordered the US military to \"shoot and kill\" any Iranian boats caught laying mines in the Strait of Hormuz. The Pentagon is simultaneously developing multiple attack plans targeting Iranian forces around the strait, the southern Arabian Gulf, and the Gulf of Oman.\n\n- **The Lebanon extension:** Trump extended the Israel-Lebanon ceasefire for three weeks following White House discussions with both countries' ambassadors. He said \"time is not on Tehran's side.\"\n- **The Hormuz escalation:** Iranian mine-laying operations are now classified as military targets, not shipping hazards to navigate around. Several attack scenarios are under active Pentagon review.\n\n*Trump extended a ceasefire and issued a shoot-to-kill order in the same press cycle. De-escalation is a spectrum.*\n\n**Sources:** [NBC News](https://www.nbcnews.com/world/iran/live-blog/live-updates-trump-iran-hormuz-blockade-ceasefire-talks-lebanon-israel-rcna341571) | [CBS News](https://www.cbsnews.com/live-updates/iran-war-trump-video-strait-of-hormuz-ship-attack-ceasefire-lebanon/) | [Al Jazeera](https://www.aljazeera.com/news/liveblog/2026/4/24/iran-war-live-lebanon-truce-extended-trump-says-time-not-on-tehrans-side)\n\n---\n\n## 🪖 The Pentagon Is Floating Suspending Spain from NATO Over the Iran War\n\nAn internal Pentagon email obtained April 24 proposes suspending Spain from NATO over its refusal to support US operations against Iran — Spain declined to provide access, bases, or overflight rights. The same memo floats reviewing the US position on Britain's claim to the Falkland Islands.\n\n- **Spain's position:** Defense Minister Margarita Robles called the war \"profoundly illegal and unjust.\" PM Sanchez has held this line despite Trump's tariff threats.\n- **The Pentagon's framing:** \"The War Department will ensure that the President has credible options to ensure that our allies are no longer a paper tiger.\"\n\n*A founding NATO member may get suspended for not joining a war the US started. Article 5 was apparently a one-way commitment all along.*\n\n**Sources:** [CNBC](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/04/24/pentagon-email-floats-suspending-spain-from-nato-other-steps-over-iran-rift-reuters-reports.html) | [The Irish Times](https://www.irishtimes.com/world/us/2026/04/24/pentagon-email-floats-suspending-spain-from-nato-over-iran-rift-source-says/) | [Al-Monitor](https://www.al-monitor.com/originals/2026/04/exclusive-pentagon-email-floats-suspending-spain-nato-other-steps-over-iran-rift)\n\n---\n\n## 📜 The EU Just Approved Its 20th Russia Sanctions Package\n\nThe EU formally approved its 20th round of Russia sanctions on April 23, targeting energy revenues, the military-industrial complex, trade, financial services, and — for the first time explicitly — cryptocurrency.\n\n- **The number:** Twenty packages in four years. Each announced with gravity. Russia's GDP contracted 3.1% in 2025. The war is now in its fifth year.\n- **What's new:** Crypto joins the financial targeting, closing a channel that had been used to route money around earlier packages.\n\n*Twenty sanctions packages. The EU is running out of things to sanction and Russia is running out of things to cut before hitting bone.*\n\n**Sources:** [Council of the EU](https://www.consilium.europa.eu/en/press/press-releases/2026/04/23/russia-s-war-of-aggression-against-ukraine-20th-round-of-stern-eu-sanctions-hits-energy-military-industrial-complex-trade-and-financial-services-including-crypto/)\n\n---\n\n## 💶 The EU Approved €90 Billion for Ukraine. It Only Took Months of Deadlock.\n\nThe EU finalized a €90 billion (~$105 billion) financial support package for Ukraine on April 23, ending months of political gridlock. Disbursements begin in Q2 2026.\n\n- **The delay:** No single country officially blocked it, but \"months of deadlock\" to pass emergency wartime funding is its own kind of commentary on EU governance.\n- **The scale:** €90 billion is more than half Ukraine's pre-war annual GDP (~€160 billion). Combined with previous tranches and US military aid, Ukraine's international support is now measured in nine figures per quarter.\n\n*The EU passed €90B for Ukraine after months of gridlock. The war did not gridlock.*\n\n**Sources:** [NPR](https://www.npr.org/2026/04/23/nx-s1-5796719/iran-middle-east-updates)"
  }
